You can get the kind from the object. All top-level api objects have an implicit `unversioned.TypeMeta`, so you should be able to determine the kind or alias by writing a helper function like

```
func getKindFor(obj *unversioned.TypeMeta) string {
    kindName := obj.GroupVersionKind().Kind
    if alias, ok := ResourceShortFormFor(kindName); ok {
                kindName = alias
    } else if kindName == "" {
        kindName = "unknown"
    }
    return kindName
}
```

I suggest you do something like the above to determine the kind name and alias inside each `print` call. You do still have to pass a `WithKind` bool in options, but that's reasonable.

